title: The Peter Stuyvesant, Northeast corner Riverside Drive and 98th Street. (In course of construction.)
The Chesterfield. North Corner of Riverside Drive and Ninety-eighth Street.
Peter Stuyvesant. South Corner Ninety-eighth Street and Riverside Drive.

text:
Riverside Park, north from a point in same near West 98th Street. This set consists of 3 views; Nos. 2 and 3 being slightly northward. Note the New York Central Railroad tracks that parallel the river. In 1938 these will be lost to view; the West Side Improvement Project causing same to be moved eastward and covered in.

June 17, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
